{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A static prompt-template lint check rejects phase-specific instruction leakage copied from SKILL.md.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is between multiple local modules: template discovery, SKILL.md snippet source, and lint-rule matching. A unit test of only the matcher can miss regressions in file loading/path wiring that let leaked instructions pass.","test_description":"Run the real lint entrypoint against fixture prompt-template files plus a fixture SKILL.md section. Include one template with copied phase instructions and assert lint fails with the expected violation; include a clean template and assert pass.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The fully assembled prompt produced by the real test harness (after interpolation/fixtures) still contains no phase-instruction leakage.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Leakage can be introduced during interpolation/fixture merge, which is a module-handoff issue. Unit-testing template strings alone would miss assembly-time concatenation bugs.","test_description":"Execute the real prompt-assembly pipeline with representative fixtures/variables, capture the final prompt text, and assert it does not contain phase-instruction spans derived from SKILL.md.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The test invocation loads skill context from the plugin/skill files and validates behavior from that context rather than from hard-coded prompt rules.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is specifically about proving dependency on real local skill/plugin files. Mocked loaders or hard-coded strings can hide a real wiring failure where context is not actually loaded.","test_description":"Run the invocation through the real loader using fixture plugin/skill directories, then assert the resolved context includes expected skill content fingerprints and that no hard-coded phase-rule block is injected by the test prompt builder.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"If the relevant SKILL.md section is removed or degraded, the behavioral test fails with the same user-style prompt.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on behavior changing when real skill context quality changes. That requires a real model call and tolerating non-deterministic outcomes; pure integration mocks can pass while missing true behavior drift.","test_description":"Run the same behavioral smoke test prompt twice against the real model path: once with intact SKILL.md and once with degraded/removed section. Assert pass in baseline and fail (or materially worse score) in degraded condition under a statistically robust threshold/retry policy.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Raw model output is captured to a diagnostic artifact before any JSON parsing or extraction logic runs.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The risk is ordering across components (inference response handling, artifact writer, parser). A unit test of parser or logger alone would not prove pre-parse capture happens in the real call flow.","test_description":"Execute one real harness run (model can be stubbed deterministically), then assert a raw-output artifact is written and contains the unparsed response bytes/text before parser invocation; verify by forcing parser failure and confirming artifact still exists.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Assertions verify structured behavior (for example field placement or schema shape), not mere keyword presence that could come from prompt echoing.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"The core failure boundary is assertion logic quality. You can catch false-positive keyword checks with crafted local outputs (including prompt-echo text) without real I/O.","test_description":"Unit-test assertion helpers with adversarial fixtures: one output containing required keywords in echoed prose but wrong schema/field placement (must fail), and one output with correct structure (must pass).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.62,"Integration":0.28,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
